<title>ITALY: Italy's Turin sees August CPI at 3.0 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Italy's Turin sees August CPI at 3.0 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>TURIN, Italy 1996-08-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Turin said its August consumer price index rose 0.1 percent month-on-month and up 3.0 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>In July, Turin's inflation rate was 0.1 percent and 3.3 percent respectively.</p>
<p>Turin is one of 10 Italian cities publishing the inflation data over the next three days.</p>
<p>The city's CPI has a weighting of 8.81 percent on the national index. The 10 sample cities have a combined weighting of 69.67 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>Following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to July 1996):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.1   (0.1)     3.0  (3.3)</p>
<p>    Food				 -0.2   (0.4)     4.8  (4.5)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.0   (0.0)     5.0  (5.1)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   0.5   (0.1)     2.7  (2.2)</p>
<p>    Furniture			  -0.1   (0.1)     1.0  (1.7)</p>
<p>    Health services		   0.0  (-0.1)     1.3  (1.2)</p>
<p>    Transportation		    0.2   (0.2)     3.2  (4.6)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture     0.2   (0.0)     3.6  (4.0)</p>
<p>    Education			   0.0   (0.0)     4.2  (4.2)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.1   (0.1)     1.7  (1.9)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	 0.3   (0.2)     2.3  (2.6)</p>
<p>-- Milan newsroom ++392 66129526</p>
